<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
SparkLine Demo
</Paragraph>


<Paragraph>This sample illustrates the sparkline configuration implemented using Essential Chart.</Paragraph>

<Paragraph>A sparkline is a type of information graphic characterized by its small size and high data density. Sparklines present trends and variations associated with some measurement, such as average temperature or stock market activity, in a simple and condensed way. Several sparklines are often used together as elements of a small multiple.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph TextAlignment ="Center"><Image Source="Images/Sparklinedemo.png" Height="600" Width="750" /></Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Features
</Paragraph>

<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Sparkline has the following types like <Bold>Line</Bold>, <Bold>Column</Bold> and <Bold>Win/Loss</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Markers helps to mark the points in line. </Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Essential Chart Sparkline supports customization of sparkline like indicating <Bold>High point</Bold>, <Bold>Low Point</Bold>, <Bold>First Point</Bold>, <Bold>Last Point</Bold>, <Bold>Negative Point</Bold>, <Bold>RangeBand</Bold> and <Bold>RangeBand Interior</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>RangeBand is used to customize particular range of the chart </Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Interactive Features</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">

<ListItem>
<Paragraph> The <Bold>Type</Bold> of the sparkline can be set by clicking the type buttons available in the ribbon. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The Check box <Bold>"High Point"</Bold> indicates the high point value in the sparkline. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The Check box <Bold>"Low Point"</Bold> indicates the low point value in the sparkline. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The Check box <Bold>"Negative Point"</Bold> indicates the negative point value in the sparkline. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The Check box <Bold>"First Point"</Bold> indicates the starting point value in the sparkline. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The Check box <Bold>"Last Point"</Bold> indicates the Last point value in the sparkline. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The Check box <Bold>"EnableRangeBand"</Bold> used to enable and disable the RangeBand. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The ColorPicker <Bold>"RangeBand Color"</Bold> Used to change the interior of the RangeBand. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>


<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The <Bold>"Style"</Bold> of the sparkline can be changed by choosing the styles available in the list box. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>

</List>

